Package com.authlete.cose

Class SigStructure

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.authlete.cbor.CBORItem
      • com.authlete.cbor.CBORItemList
        • com.authlete.cose.SigStructure
  • public class SigStructure
extends CBORItemList
    Sig Signature

    This class represents Sig_structure which is defined in 4.4. Signing and Verification Process of RFC 9052 as follows. 

     Sig_structure = [
     context : "Signature" / "Signature1",
     body_protected : empty_or_serialized_map,
     ? sign_protected : empty_or_serialized_map,
     external_aad : bstr,
     payload : bstr
 ]
    Since:
    1.1
    See Also:
    RFC 9052, 4.4. Signing and Verification Process, SigStructureBuilder

    • Constructor Detail

      • SigStructure

        public SigStructure​(COSEProtectedHeader bodyAttributes,
                    COSEProtectedHeader signerAttributes,
                    CBORByteArray externalData,
                    CBORItem payload)
        A constructor with the protected header of the content, the protected header of COSE_Signature, the external data and the payload.

        This constructor is for COSE_Sign.

        The type of the payload argument has been changed from CBORByteArray to CBORItem since version 1.5. This is because the ISO/IEC 18013-5:2021 standard requires that the payload start with a tag instead of a byte string.

        Parameters:
        bodyAttributes - The protected header of the content. Must not be null.
        signerAttributes - The protected header of COSE_Signature. Must not be null.
        externalData - The external data.
        payload - The payload.

        externalData - The external data.
        payload - The payload.
